  "body_text": null,
  "page": null,
  "source": "[\\set.theoretic.power.set{X}]\nDefines: P is \\set\nwhen: X is \\set\nexpresses:\n. forAll: A is \\set\n  then:\n  . have: A \\:subset?:/ X\n    iff: A \"in\" P\nDocumented:\n. called: \"power set of $X?$\"\n. written: \"\\mathcal{P}(X?)\"\n. description: \"The power set $\\mathcal{P}(X)$, guaranteed by the axiom of powers: for every set $X$ there exists a set $\\mathcal{P}(X)$ such that $A \\in \\mathcal{P}(X)$ if and only if $A \\subseteq X$.\"\nId: \"dfc8cab3-42ba-44b3-8da0-b58717abeb61\"",
